                            <comment id="319829" author="adilger" created="Thu, 2 Dec 2021 00:30:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Problem is definitely in patch, which has repeatedly hit the same failures for each version, and is the only patch failing those tests.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;replay-single test_65b has 6 failures in 4 weeks for this patch, no other failures: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/search?status%5B%5D=FAIL&amp;amp;test_set_script_id=f6a12204-32c3-11e0-a61c-52540025f9ae&amp;amp;sub_test_script_id=51923c9a-4a46-11e0-a7f6-52540025f9af&amp;amp;start_date=2021-11-01&amp;amp;end_date=2021-12-01&amp;amp;source=sub_tests#redirect&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/search?status%5B%5D=FAIL&amp;amp;test_set_script_id=f6a12204-32c3-11e0-a61c-52540025f9ae&amp;amp;sub_test_script_id=51923c9a-4a46-11e0-a7f6-52540025f9af&amp;amp;start_date=2021-11-01&amp;amp;end_date=2021-12-01&amp;amp;source=sub_tests#redirect&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;recovery-small test_106 has 4 failures for this patch, no other failures: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/search?status%5B%5D=FAIL&amp;amp;test_set_script_id=f36cabd0-32c3-11e0-a61c-52540025f9ae&amp;amp;sub_test_script_id=ae5ad366-c960-11e1-a79d-52540035b04c&amp;amp;start_date=2021-11-01&amp;amp;end_date=2021-12-01&amp;amp;source=sub_tests#redirect&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/search?status%5B%5D=FAIL&amp;amp;test_set_script_id=f36cabd0-32c3-11e0-a61c-52540025f9ae&amp;amp;sub_test_script_id=ae5ad366-c960-11e1-a79d-52540035b04c&amp;amp;start_date=2021-11-01&amp;amp;end_date=2021-12-01&amp;amp;source=sub_tests#redirect&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;conf-sanity test_35b has 3 failures for this patch, no other failures: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/search?status%5B%5D=FAIL&amp;amp;test_set_script_id=7f66aa20-3db2-11e0-80c0-52540025f9af&amp;amp;sub_test_script_id=829bdbb6-3db2-11e0-80c0-52540025f9af&amp;amp;start_date=2021-11-23&amp;amp;end_date=2021-12-01&amp;amp;source=sub_tests#redirect&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/search?status%5B%5D=FAIL&amp;amp;test_set_script_id=7f66aa20-3db2-11e0-80c0-52540025f9af&amp;amp;sub_test_script_id=829bdbb6-3db2-11e0-80c0-52540025f9af&amp;amp;start_date=2021-11-23&amp;amp;end_date=2021-12-01&amp;amp;source=sub_tests#redirect&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="319824" author="adilger" created="Thu, 2 Dec 2021 00:00:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;James, given that the patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/41664&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/41664&lt;/a&gt; &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14428&quot; title=&quot;Convert tracefile to use ring_buffer  from linux&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-14428&quot;&gt;LU-14428&lt;/a&gt; libcfs: replace tracefile buffer with ring_buffer&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; being tested is modifying the debug logging, and this test failed because a specific message was not logged in the debug buffer, I&apos;m inclined to think that the problem is a regression in the patch itself.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
